The paper discusses a method for proving failure of queries for definite logic programs using XSB-Prolog. This involves using a model generator for first order logic and exploiting the peculiarities of definite programs to obtain a better solution. These topics are closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), databases (cs.DB), and software engineering (cs.SE).
